Package: mathmagic
Type: Package
Title: This package contains functions that perform math tricks
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: Shannon Fischer
Maintainer: fischer132@usf.edu
Description: This package contains several functions that perform "math magic" or "number tricks".
This is when you pick a number within a set of parameters, perform a series of calculations on that number,
and it will have a specific result. This package is meant for entertainment purposes. These functions were 
created base off https://www.thoughtco.com/math-tricks-that-will-blow-your-mind-4154742 and https://www.educationworld.com/a_curr/mathchat/mathchat012.shtml.

Functions;

Thought CO. # 1
mm1 - If you multiply 6 by an even, single digit number greater that zero, the answer will end with the same digit. 
The number in the ten's place will be half of the number in the one's place. 

Thought CO. # 4
mm2 - Take any three-digit number and write it twice to make a six-digit number. Divide the number by 7. 
Divide it by 11. Divide it by 13.The order in which you do the division is unimportant. 
The answer is the three-digit number. 

Thought CO. # 7
mm3 - Select a number from 1 to 6. Multiply the number by 9. Multiply it by 111. Multiply it by 1001.
Divide the answer by 7. The number will contain the digits 1, 2, 4, 5, 7, and 8.  

Education World # 5
mm4 - Here is a magic number: 12,345,679. Pick a number from 1 to 9. Multiply your number by 9.
Multiply the magic number by your new number. The result is a string of nine digits made up entirely of
your starting number.

